- Initialize a loop from 1 up to 100. (I include 100 as usually in such problems, the maximum value is inclusive).
- For each iteration:
   - If the current number i is divisible by both 3 and 5, print "FizzBuzz"
   - Else if it is only divisible by 3, print "Fizz"
   - Else if it's only divisible by 5, print "Buzz"
   - If none of these conditions are satisfied i.e., it's neither divisible by 3 nor 5, simply print the number itself.

Here is the JavaScript code implementing this logic:

```javascript
for(let i=1; i<=100; i++){
    if(i % (3*5) === 0)
        console.log("FizzBuzz");
    else if(i % 3 === 0)
        console.log("Fizz");
    else if(i % 5 === 0)
        console.log("Buzz");
    else
        console.log(i);
}
```

